description:
This Prospect Heights apartment is both comfortable and conveniently located close to major Brooklyn attractions.

This Prospect Heights space is comfortable. Situated 2 landings up is bright apt with many amenities starting with the entryway table full of food delivery menus, subway maps, and "Things to do in NYC" pamphlets to the Kitchen which over looks the garden stocked with basic ingredients, pots and pans, coffee, variety of teas and iron.

Guest will have a private entrance to the apt upstairs

Interaction with guest will probably be minimal, but available to answer any questions.

Situated so close to Everything Brooklyn makes this location so convenient. 
On Saturday's you can walk to the famous Brooklyn Flea to eat the local fare and people watch or stroll through Prospect Park which is directly next to 
The Brooklyn Museum and The Botanical Garden. 
You can catch a movie or play at the majestic Brooklyn Academy of Music or 
a Nets game or Concert at the Barclays Center and shopping at the Atlantic Center 
On the way home you can stop by one of the countless Restaurants and Cafes. 
Coffee Houses and Bars or Supermarkets
So much to choose from close Vanderbilt Ave, Washington Ave, Franklin Ave, Dekalb Aves, 
to name a few.
Go explore! Our place will be waiting.

Close to the 8th Ave line, 
City buses throughout and 
cityBikes for rental close by.
Uber
Green n Yellow metered cabs
Sidewalks for walking

Ceiling fans in every room. 
Many Brooklyn neighborhoods are under constant construction including this one. So you may expect construction noise around 8am-4:30pm During the week.
Free coffee and variety of teas

hosts.about:
Born and raised in Brooklyn where I call home. I've enjoyed amazing places outside of New York: from the Islands of the Caribbean to the ski Slopes in Quebec and Utah.
There's no where else I'd rather live and I hope your stay with us is just as enthusiastic in our family run home!
